docs {
  # Get Single Health Tip

  Retrieves detailed information for a specific health tip by its ID.

  ## Path Parameters

  - `id` (string, required): The unique identifier of the health tip
    - Example: `350` for "Get Tested for Chlamydia and Gonorrhea"

  ## Success Response (200 OK)

  ```json
  {
    "status": "success",
    "message": "Health tip retrieved successfully",
    "data": {
      "id": "350",
      "title": "Get Tested for Chlamydia and Gonorrhea",
      "imageUrl": "https://odphp.health.gov/sites/default/files/2024-01/Get_Tested_Chlamydia_Gonorrhea.jpg",
      "imageAlt": "A man and woman smiling",
      "lastUpdated": "10/21/2025 3:45:54 PM",
      "mainContent": [
        {
          "title": "The Basics: Overview",
          "content": "<p>Chlamydia and gonorrhea are sexually transmitted infections...</p>"
        },
        {
          "title": "The Basics: Who Needs Testing?",
          "content": "<h4>Who needs to get tested for chlamydia and gonorrhea?</h4>..."
        },
        {
          "title": "Take Action: Get Tested",
          "content": "<p>Get tested for chlamydia and gonorrhea if you're at risk...</p>"
        }
      ]
    }
  }
  ```

  ## Error Response (422 Validation Error)

  ```json
  {
    "status": "error",
    "message": "Validation Error: ✖ Required → at id",
    "errors": {
      "id": ["Required"]
    }
  }
  ```

  ## Error Response (404 Not Found)

  If the health tip doesn't exist in the external API:

  ```json
  {
    "status": "error",
    "message": "Health tip not found"
  }
  ```
}
